  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best ways to cook winkles?",
  "response": "Winkles, also known as periwinkles, are small edible sea snails. They have a pleasant, slightly salty flavor and can be cooked in various ways. Here are some of the best methods to prepare winkles:\n\n1. **Boiling**:\n   - **Preparation**: Rinse winkles thoroughly under cold running water to remove any sand or debris. You may need to soak them in salt water to expel any remaining sand.\n   - **Boiling Process**: Bring a pot of salted water to a rolling boil. Add winkles to the boiling water and cook for about 5 to 10 minutes until they are tender and easily removed from their shells.\n   - **Serving**: Drain the boiled winkles and serve with melted butter, garlic, and herbs for dipping, or simply enjoy them plain.\n\n2. **Steaming**:\n   - **Preparation**: Clean the winkles as described above.\n   - **Steaming Process**: Place them in a steamer basket over boiling water. Steam for about 5 to 10 minutes until they are cooked through and easily extracted from their shells.\n   - **Serving**: Serve with a dipping sauce made from butter and herbs or a lemon-garlic butter sauce.\n\n3. **Saut\u00e9ing**:\n   - **Preparation**: Clean winkles and boil them briefly to make them easier to extract from their shells.\n   - **Saut\u00e9ing Process**: Remove winkles from shells with a toothpick or small fork. Heat a pan with butter or olive oil, adding garlic, onions, or other aromatic vegetables. Add the winkles and saut\u00e9 for a few minutes until they are infused with the flavors.\n   - **Serving**: Serve as an appetizer or include them in a larger dish, like pasta or rice.\n\n4. **Grilling**:\n   - **Preparation**: Clean and boiling winkles can make extraction from their shells easier.\n   - **Grilling Process**: Extract winkles from their shells and skewer them on sticks. Brush with olive oil, garlic, lemon juice, and herbs. Grill over medium heat for a few minutes until they are cooked through and lightly charred.\n   - **Serving**: Serve with additional lemon or dipping sauce.\n\n5. **In a Broth or Soup**:\n   - **Preparation**: Clean the winkles thoroughly.\n   - **Cooking Process**: Boil the winkles as described above, then add them to your favorite seafood broth or soup. They can be added whole or extracted from their shells before adding to the soup.\n   - **Serving**: Serve as part of a seafood chowder or Mediterranean-style soup.\n\nDifferent regions may have variations on these methods, incorporating local herbs and spices to enhance the flavor. Enjoy experimenting with winkles and finding the preparation method that suits your taste! \n\nRemember to check if winkles are sustainably sourced, as it's important to support responsible seafood harvesting practices.",
